          <div class="trac-modifiedby"><a href="/wiki/WikiStart?action=diff&amp;version=173" title="Version 173 by jreed: link to latest release">Last modified</a> <a class="timeline" href="/timeline?from=2013-06-14T16%3A22%3A55Z&amp;precision=second" title="2013-06-14T16:22:55Z in Timeline">2 months</a> ago</div>
          <div id="wikipage"><h1 id="BIND10">BIND 10</h1>
<p>
<strong>BIND 10 is the next generation of BIND, the most widely-used DNS server on the Internet. BIND 10 is a five year development project, beginning year four on 2012-04-01. BIND 10 1.1.0 for the Authoritative server is here!
</strong>
</p>
<ul><li>For more details on the contents of the release: <a href="http://bind10.isc.org/wiki/ProductionRelease">http://bind10.isc.org/wiki/ProductionRelease</a>
</li><li>To download the release: <a class="ext-link" href="ftp://ftp.isc.org/isc/bind10/1.1.0/bind10-1.1.0.tar.gz"><span class="icon"> </span>ftp://ftp.isc.org/isc/bind10/1.1.0/bind10-1.1.0.tar.gz</a>
</li><li>To discuss your testing with the bind 10 user community: <a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-users"><span class="icon"> </span>https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-users</a>
</li></ul><p>
<em>Easy installation directions are on the <a class="wiki" href="/wiki/InstallStartPage">Installation Start Page</a>.</em>
</p>
<p>
The <a class="wiki" href="/wiki/ComponentStatus">component status</a> page describes the status of the various parts of the system.
</p>
<div style="font-size: 18px" class="wikipage"><p>
If you are...
</p>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>interested in following news about BIND 10</em>, join the <a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-announce"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 Announcement list</a>, check out our <a class="wiki" href="/wiki/NewsMedia">NewsMedia</a>, or read  the <a class="ext-link" href="http://www.isc.org/blog/category/bind-10"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 category</a> of the <a class="ext-link" href="http://www.isc.org/community/blogs"><span class="icon"> </span>ISC Blogs</a>.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>interested in trying out BIND 10</em>, download the <a class="ext-link" href="ftp://ftp.isc.org/isc/bind10/latest/"><span class="icon"> </span>latest version</a>, check it out from <a class="wiki" href="/wiki/GitGuidelines">the repository</a>, join the <a href="http://bind10.isc.org/wiki/external_test">External Test Program</a> or start with the <a href="http://bind10.isc.org/docs/bind10-guide.html">BIND 10 Guide</a>.  See also <a href="http://bind10.isc.org/wiki/SystemSpecificNotes">hints for building BIND 10</a> specific to some operating systems.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>reporting a bug</em>, create an account on this web site, then click <a href="http://bind10.isc.org/newticket">New Ticket</a> at the top.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>interested in joining our generous sponsors and donors</em>, visit <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.isc.org/bind10/sponsors/"><span class="icon"> </span>https://www.isc.org/bind10/sponsors/</a>.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>interested in being a BIND 10 developer</em>, check out the resources below and make sure to join the <a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-dev"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 Developers list</a>.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>a core BIND 10 developer</em>, visit key developer resources (coming soon).
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><div style="border: 2px solid #ded; background: #efe; margin-bottom: 10px; -moz-border-radius: 10px; -webkit-border-radius: 10px" class="wikipage"><blockquote>
<p>
...<em>none of the above</em>, possibly you should go to the <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.isc.org/wordpress/software/bind10/"><span class="icon"> </span>ISC BIND 10 page</a> our main web site.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div><h2 id="CommunicationCollaboration">Communication &amp; Collaboration</h2>
<ul><li><a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-announce"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 Announcement list</a> - low-volume e-mail list, mostly release announcements
</li><li><a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-users"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 Users list</a> - e-mail list for BIND 10 users, currently very low volume
</li><li><a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-dev"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 Developers list</a> - e-mail list for BIND 10 developers, gets several posts a day about BIND 10 development details
</li><li><a class="ext-link" href="https://lists.isc.org/mailman/listinfo/bind10-dhcp"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 DHCP Developers list</a> - e-mail list for discussions specific to DHCP development
</li><li>BIND 10 <a class="wiki" href="/wiki/Jabber">Jabber</a> room, xmpp:bind10@conference.jabber.isc.org, where the BIND 10 developers hang out
</li><li><a class="wiki" href="/wiki/NewsMedia">NewsMedia</a> - articles about BIND 10
</li><li>The <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.isc.org/community/blogs"><span class="icon"> </span>ISC Blogs</a> have a <a class="ext-link" href="https://www.isc.org/blog/category/bind-10"><span class="icon"> </span>BIND 10 category</a>
</li><li><a class="wiki" href="/wiki/Presentations">Presentations</a> - presentations about BIND 10
</li><li><a class="wiki" href="/wiki/Scrum">Scrum</a> Scrum resources - more about the agile methodology BIND 10 uses.
</li></ul><h2 id="Development">Development</h2>
<ul><li><a class="wiki" href="/wiki/DesignOverview">DesignOverview</a>
